{"word":"σωφρονέω","slug":"σωφρονέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>σωφρονέω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:σώφρων\">σώφρων</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘be in one’s right mind’, as opposed to being deranged <b><a href='B:480 5:15'>Mk 5:15</a>; <a href='B:490 8:35'>Lk 8:35</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ sim.\">sim.</a> as opposite of being out of one’s mind <b><a href='B:540 5:13'>2 Cor 5:13</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘use good sense’, <b>be sensible <a href='B:520 12:3'>Ro 12:3</a>; <a href='B:630 2:6'>Tit 2:6</a>; <a href='B:670 4:7'>1 Pt 4:7</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:σωτήριος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:σωφρονίζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}